-- Bright Dairy Will Pay $58 Million for 51% Stake in New Zealand's Synlait
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-18T22:48:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-18/bright-dairy-will-pay-58-million-for-51-stake-in-new-zealand-s-synlait.html

          
          
             Bright Dairy & Food Co. plans to pay
NZ$82 million ($58 million) for a 51 percent stake in Synlait
Milk Ltd. of New Zealand, the Chinese dairy company said in a
statement to the Shanghai stock exchange today.  
 Bright Dairy will buy 26 million shares in Synlait, which
is 22.5 percent owned by Japanâ€™s Mitsui & Co., for NZ$3.15 a
share, according to the statement.  
